- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on Fully Homomorphic Encryption (FHE) which is a cryptographic technique.
- cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) is also likely as the paper presents a novel hardware architecture for FHE.
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) is relevant as the paper discusses the computation overhead of FHE and proposes a solution to improve its performance.
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is less likely but still possible as the paper may discuss programming languages used in the implementation of the proposed architecture.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also less likely but possible as the paper may discuss the system-level design of the proposed architecture.
